<h2>Are there any Fibromyalgia Causes that we know of? Do we know what they are?</h2>
<p>There is much research at this time regarding fibromyalgia causes and its affects on the body. The problem is that no one can seem to agree on what the exact fibromyalgia causes are.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">Fibromyalgia causes and the theories behind them.</h2>
<p>There are studies that state that one of the fibromyalgia causes is that it is hereditary which means that <em>it may be a genetic syndrome for most but not all fibromyalgia patients.</em></p>
<p>Another study is taking into consideration that <em>hormonal or chemical imbalances may effect nerve communication.</em></p>
<p>Many other experts believe that the muscle pain may have something to do with stress brought on by some kind of illness or trauma.</p>
<p>What we do know is that one of the fibromyalgia causes which causes the chronic pain is probably the result of lowered serotonin, which of course can lower pain thresholds.</p>
<p>While all of these theories may come to play out, for now there are no real answers that are 100% definitive. Although there is no clear-cut cause for fibromyalgia causes, we certainly have learned a lot about the effects.</p>
<p>Fibromyalgia causes are causing controversy.</p>
<h2>Some of the misconceptions of Fibromyalgia Causes and Diagnosis.</h2>
<p>Without knowing the fibromyalgia causes, the most common misconception of fibromyalgia is that it is not a real illness or that it is all in the patient’s head. Well there are certain criteria’s to be met to have the fibromyalgia diagnosis.</p>
<p>To meet the criteria for the fibromyalgia diagnosis, there are certain painful tender points above and below the waist on both sides of the body that are painful to the touch.</p>
<p>In people who have fibromyalgia, the pain signals between the brain and the spinal cord process are heightened and so the sensitivity to pain is strong even just to the touch.</p>
<h2>Have any of the misconceptions changed over the years?</h2>
<p>More and more people believe that fibromyalgia is a real medical condition although the fibromyalgia causes are not yet obvious but what is obvious is that fibromyalgia causes are important to find in order to cure.</p>
<p>Let’s face it; if it weren’t a real condition, the pharmaceutical companies wouldn’t be working so hard on medications as a fibromyalgia treatment.</p>
<p>Medical professionals, especially Rheumatologist along with chiropractors, acupuncturists, massage therapists feel that knowing the fibromyalgia causes  would be great but it is up to them to treat the chronic fibromyalgia symptoms.</p>
<h2>What are Some of the Fibromyalgia symptoms?</h2>
<p>There are many chronic effects of Fibromyalgia. Many of these flares up can include fibromyalgia symptoms<strong> </strong>like <em>irritable bowel syndrome, chronic fatigue syndrome</em> and of course <em>fibromyalgia chronic fatigue just to name a few.</em></p>
<p>The list of symptoms can include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Insomnia</li>
<li>Overall pain (from head to toe)</li>
<li>Chronic fatigue</li>
<li>Irritable bowel</li>
<li>Fibro fog (memory and concentration problems)</li>
<li>Urinary tract infections</li>
<li>Painful menses</li>
<li>Headaches/Migraines</li>
<li>Depression</li>
<li>Weight gain</li>
<li>Anxiety</li>
<li>Muscle stiffness</li>
</ul>
<p>These symptoms and more make up this complex syndrome. The Fibromyalgia causes? Unknown!</p>
<p>For this reason, Fibromyalgia specialists also known as <strong>Rheumatologists</strong> offer many Fibromyalgia treatments however, don&#8217;t expect to find out what the Fibromyalgia Causes are.</p>
<h2>What are the Recommended Fibromyalgia Treatments?</h2>
<p>Rheumatologists can help to a certain extent with prescription drugs to help with pain and depression. However, even those don&#8217;t always contain and help this condition to its fullest.</p>
<p>There are many new drugs on the market to help with chronic pain, insomnia and depression from fibromyalgia, the problem becomes that these drugs have side effects.</p>
<p>What if the prescription drugs are helping the symptoms but since we don&#8217;t know the fibromyalgia causes, <strong>could they be hurting us?</strong></p>
<p>Well that&#8217;s a question that we can only hope to answer in the future. Until we know what the Fibromyalgia causes are, I don&#8217;t think a cure is in sight.</p>
<h2>Most times prescriptions drugs are used in conjunction with the following:</h2>
<ul>
<li>Chiropractic care</li>
<li>Aqua therapy</li>
<li>Acupuncture</li>
<li>Natural Alternative Herbal Supplements</li>
<li>Yoga</li>
<li>Meditation</li>
<li>Acupressure</li>
<li>Meditation</li>
<li>Yoga</li>
<li>Light Exercise</li>
</ul>
<h2>Stress Relief in The Fibromyalgia Patient.</h2>
<p>Stress and anxiety can play an integral role in the day-to-day function of a fibromyalgia patient.</p>
<p><em><strong>Stress increases the pain sensitivity</strong></em> and the ability to work through the pain.</p>
<p><em>Meditating once a day for just 10 minutes can make a huge difference</em> in the daily life of a fibromyalgia patient.</p>
<p><em>Yoga is another way to reduce stress and anxiety</em> and to stretch out the muscles for pain relief.</p>
<h2>More Fibromyalgia Treatments to consider:</h2>
<p>While we continue to wait and find out what the fibromyalgia causes are, we still have to live.</p>
<p><em>Aqua therapy can help with loosening up the muscles</em> that are constantly contracting and causing pain.</p>
<p><em>Chiropractic care</em> can be an essential part of the Fibromyalgia treatment option. Chiropractors have been able to discover and implement many different options for treating chronic pain.</p>
<p>Some Chiropractors will use adjustments with ultrasound healing therapy while others will use adjustments with laser therapy and more.<br />
Whatever methods they use will help in the continual management of chronic pain.</p>
<h2>Once the Fibromyalgia Diagnosis is made:</h2>
<p>Having the Fibromyalgia diagnosis made, can of course be devastating, however, <strong>remember that this is not a life threatening illness and to some degree </strong>the fibromyalgia causes don&#8217;t really matter as long as you get treatment and pain relief.</p>
<p> <div style="width:690px ;margin-left :100 px;"><div style="margin-top:50px; float: left;"><script type="text/javascript"><!--
