</div>It is an illness that is managed by Fibromyalgia Specialists so that the fibromyalgia patient can function on a daily basis. Take ongoing steps to avoid “flare ups” and be conscious what your body is telling you.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong><strong>Don’t overdo it when you are feeling good</strong></strong></li>
<li>Know your body and your limits</li>
<li><strong><strong>Use all the resources that are available to you</strong></strong></li>
<li>Get messages as often as you can</li>
<li><strong><strong>Find a good chiropractor</strong></strong></li>
<li>Use aqua therapy</li>
<li><strong><strong>Learn to mediate even just for a few minutes a day</strong></strong></li>
<li>Learn to do yoga</li>
<li><strong>Make every attempt to do some light exercise or walking every day</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>There are many pain clinics available that are fibromyalgia specialists and most insurance plans will pay for treatment.</p>
<p>Remember that fibromyalgia causes are being researched and eventually will be found. Whatever those fibromyalgia causes are, hopefully they will help with a cure.</p>
<p>Don&#8217;t sell your body short and don&#8217;t give up. Help is coming but just remember that you have to <em>play a roll in finding what works best for you</em></p>
